Mining Manager - Indonesia
Mining Manager - Indonesia
Location:  --Jakarta
Salary:  plus bonus
FIFO In-country
Greenfields Development Project
Extensive Autonomy; Attractive Conditions
A rapidly expanding miner in SE Asia currently seeks an Mining Manager to take leadership of the group's major development project in the region.
Operating on a short FIFO in-country roster, this highly autonomous role will report to the Group CEO and take responsibility for the successful development, production and profitability of a greenfields opencut hardrock project through successful implementation of the mine plan and supervision of site works program.
An attractive remuneration package will be provided along with the opportunity to reside in Jakarta with all the abundant amenities of a bustling modern metropolis. Working for a fast emerging producer, you will be given extensive autonomy and the ability to swiftly progress your career as the company expands.
As the ideal candidate, you will have a successful and demonstrable background in managing development projects, implementing the mine plan and overseeing production for opencut hardrock operations. Significant SE Asian experience, fluency in Bahasa and substantial experience in truck & shovel operations will be greatly advantageous.
Enjoy the opportunity to lead a SE Asian development project with a fast expanding miner by clicking the apply button below.
Confidentiality assured.
